<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP20_AdventureAwaits_World" s="484088">
  <T n="category">481599<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_AdventureAwaits--></T>
  <T n="name">0x5E35D86C<!--String: "Welcome to Gibbi Point"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_World_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a14558a29d8c2eb5</T>
      <T n="text">0x4F2AD0C3<!--String: "Situated on a picturesque coastline, <font color="#199C2C"><b>Gibbi Point</b></font> is the perfect escape for those seeking adventure and relaxation. This charming region offers endless fun for the whole family who want to engage in Getaways and outdoor activities. A peculiar climate, Gibbi Point's weather sees all seasons (even snow!), however its many underground hot springs keep the waters tepid and inviting, allowing for swimming and water activities year-round."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_World_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a14558a29d8c2eb6</T>
      <T n="text">0x3BA8440F<!--String: "Nestled amidst dense wilderness, <font color="#199C2C"><b>Wanderwood Wilds</b></font> is a haven for nature enthusiasts and adventurers alike. This vibrant neighborhood offers exploration opportunities, with the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Hothead Rock Geyser</b></font>, the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Butterfly Ranger Station</b></font>, and the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Old Firewatch Tower</b></font> serving as places for Sims to explore. Kayak along serene waters and catch colorful Butterflies fluttering around.\n\nOn weekends, the <font color="#199C2C"><b>'Round the Fire</b></font> Festival brings the community together to share stories, engage with a Plumbird Expert, and savor the warmth of the campfire."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_World_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a14558a29d8c2eb7</T>
      <T n="text">0x126B4320<!--String: "<font color="#199C2C"><b>Crystal Valley</b></font>, once a bustling mining town, now offers a charming escape with its rich history and quirky attractions. Sims can <font color="#199C2C"><b>Pan for Crystals</b></font> along the shoreline, not far from the now abandoned Scoop's Gold Mine, which stands as a testament to its golden past. Visitors can unwind with the locals at the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fearful Fish Lounge</b></font>, a cozy spot for relaxation. For a unique experience, head to the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Electric Lagoon</b></font> to catch jellyfish. Keep an eye out for the elusive <font color="#199C2C"><b>Plumbird</b></font>, Pruella Preener, a local legend that adds to the valley's mystique.\n\nThe vibrant <font color="#199C2C"><b>Sunrise, Sunset</b></font> Festival, held on weekend afternoons, welcomes both the old and young with playgrounds for children and delightful activities like food, cards, and Papercrafting for everyone to enjoy."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_World_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a14558a29d8c2eb0</T>
      <T n="text">0x76EF7EC5<!--String: "<font color="#199C2C"><b>Jellyfish Junction</b></font> is a vibrant coastal neighborhood known for its thriving community of artisans and musicians. With an unmistakable arty vibe, it offers unique shops like <font color="#199C2C"><b>This Oar That Shop</b></font> for all your kayaking needs and <font color="#199C2C"><b>Makin' Paper Shop</b></font>, showcasing locally made papercrafts. The <font color="#199C2C"><b>Lonely Lighthouse</b></font> stands as a poignant spot where some Sims leave heartfelt notes.\n\n<font color="#199C2C"><b>Underlight Bay</b></font> hosts the mesmerizing <font color="#199C2C"><b>Glow and Flow Festival</b></font>, where marine life lights up the night on the new moon. For fitness enthusiasts, the docks come alive every Monday, Wednesday, and Friday with a <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fitness Fest</b></font> featuring spinning classes, weightlifting, and an Archery Contest."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
